We investigated the geographic patterns of diversity from the ESUs identified
from the barcoding data. For each ESU, when three or more locations were
sampled, we computed the convex hull to obtain a polygon approximating their
geographic distributions. We superimposed these polygons to obtain a diversity
contour map.

\subsubsection{Isolation-by-distance}

