\subsection{Geography, diversity and diversification}

The highest diversity in sea cucumbers is not the coral triangle but the Western
Pacific.

The polygon approach used to identify areas of high diversity has
limitations. In particular, it may overestimate diversity where species do not
occur but occur at the periphery. Some species included in our analysis have
restricted ranges or are known from a single specimen, and no polygons were
drawn for them. Therefore the diversity from the polygons is underestimated. For
instance, 65 species have been recorded for Guam \cite{Michonneau2013}, but
\Sexpr{sum(nSppGuam)} ESUs are estimated from the polygons.

